    <item>
      <title>Wanting less is a radical form of activism</title>
      <description>&lt;div class=&quot;poem&quot;&gt;
The two ways of getting what I want
Are having more
And wanting less

Procuring things empowers those who sell them:
To the demons of the world
Wanting less robs them of their power
As for my own shady incubi
They first writhe then fade away

New desires lead to new addictions
But contentment breeds freedom
&lt;/div&gt;
</description>
